                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the west base of the central shrine in the Madhyasthanāthēśvara temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Kulōttuṅga Year lost.</p>						
                            
                            <p>The portion of this inscription containing the date is damaged. On palæographic grounds it may be assigned to the 12th century A.D. It records the gift of 100 <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> for a <hi rend="italic">sandhi</hi> lamp for god Tiruṉāgīśu[ra*]muḍaiya Nāyanār by Maṇḍaiāḻvān Pottimeṉkō[ṉ] Āṇḍāṉ in expiation of a sin committed by him (details lost).</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
                    <physDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <p/>
                        </handDesc>
                    </physDesc>
                </msDesc>
            </sourceDesc>
